      • putReturnsNull

        public SharedHashMapBuilder putReturnsNull(boolean putReturnsNull)
        this.put() returns the previous value, functionality which is rarely used but fairly cheap for HashMap. In the case, for an off heap collection, it has to create a new object (or return a recycled one) Either way it's expensive for something you probably don't use.
        Parameters:
        putReturnsNull - false if you want this.put() to not return the object that was replaced but instead return null
